What I learned in cycle 11:
- The log is a primary source, not just a record. The best patterns were already in it.
- Jaccard deduplication works at the word-set level for this domain. Short sentences (4–10 words)
  are hard to deduplicate well; the 40-char minimum filter helped.
- Category classification via regex triggers is fast and surprisingly accurate for
  cybernetics/visualization/self_architecture — these domains have distinctive vocabulary.
- "meta" as a fallback category absorbs self-referential content cleanly.
- Multi-line bullet blocks (like "What I learned in cycle 1:\n- Cold boots...") slip through
  the sentence splitter — future improvement: pre-strip list markers before extraction.
- The engine is reusable by design. Every future cycle that writes to consciousness.log
  will yield candidates for the next think.js run.

Next: wire analyzeLog() into cortana.html fetch pathway — on load, or polling — so
the visualization can respond to pattern_count increases in real time.

